# zget: The Archival Intelligence Engine (v0.3.0)

Successfully transformed [zget](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget) from a terminal-bound script into a high-fidelity, headless archival ecosystem. This audit confirms that the transition is complete, stable, and documented for 2026 standards.

## 🏛️ Architectural Integrity
- **Headless Core**: All archival logic resides in the FastAPI backend ([src/zget/server/app.py](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/app.py)).
- **Dead Code Purged**: The `src/zget/tui` directory and its `textual` dependencies have been completely removed.
- **Streamlined CLI**: [zget](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget) now acts as a high-fidelity status browser and lightning-fast single-shot downloader.

## 📱 The Webport (PWA)
The new Webport is the primary management interface, designed with a **StoryTime** bioluminescent aesthetic.

- **Responsive Management**: Full library search and download queue monitoring on any device.
- **Share Target**: Registered in [manifest.json](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/server/static/manifest.json) to handle incoming URLs from mobile share sheets.
- **Direct Handoff**: `/api/media/{id}` allows for immediate "Save to Files" or Camera Roll ingestion on iOS/Android.

## 🤖 Agentic Readiness (MCP)
The MCP server is the "Hands" of the system, enabling other agents to use [zget](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget) as their primary archivist.

| Tool | Capability |
|------|------------|
| `zget_download` | Asynchronous high-fidelity ingestion |
| [get_local_path](file:///Users/base/Projects/zget/src/zget/mcp/tools.py#97-122) | Absolute path resolution for AI analysis (Librarian handoff) |
| `zget_search` | FTS5-powered library querying |

